Pell Street, west from a point opposite Doyers to Mott Streets, showing details of a portion of that Manhattan locality "Chinatown." 1939? Alexander Alland  NEG. # 1161 This photo is one of a series that appeared in the published volume "Portrait of N. Y." by Felix Reisenberg and Alex. Alland, IRGV.

Pell Street, west from the head of Doyers Street, to Mott Street, showing street activity in New York's Chinatown. Note the co-mingling of the Occidental and the Oriental, both in garb and advertising matter.
